  "text": "Assume that we have a generically exact Hermitian complex (2.6) in X with associated currents U and R. If π : X ′ → X is a modification, then the pullback of (2.6) is a generically exact Hermitian complex in X ′ and thus we have associated currents U ′ and R ′ . It follows from the definition, cf. [CITATION_1] , that π * U ′ = U and π * R ′ = R. In particular, if we have a Koszul complex on X generated by the section a of A * as in Example 2.3, then the pull-back is a Koszul complex in X ′ generated by the section π * a of π * A * . It follows from the example that if π * a = a 0 a ′ , where a ′ is non-vanishing, then",
